sp;<a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic><img src=http://www.firiona-vie.com/images/arfv.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a>  </td></tr><tr><td align=left></td><td align=right> <br> <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=904.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=852.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width=95%><tr><td bgcolor=#3a2220><table border=0 width=100% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=#d1c3b5 class=headings><font color=#000000>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#d1c3b5 class=headings><font color=#000000>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umistressoftherose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mistress of the Rose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Black Rose</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/01 1:43:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tinker's Pride</span><hr size=1> Hello little gnomes.  While you have always been cute you now can serve a purpose also.  If any of you are tinkerer's I will pay you for you to tinker me and item and to let me rub your bald forehead.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>I do not want any tinkered item that will blow up, kill or anything else just a simple item.  Please leave a message here as it seems I have not learned gnome yet and many of you have not learned human or dark elvish. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucasbenlightfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casben Lightfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/01 9:05:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tinker's Pride</span><hr size=1> Please send me a message, if what you seek is a simpler thing I can perhaps help you.  You may write me in the way of the human scribes, for your language is still a very foreign one to me.  <br><br>Untill then,<br>Sabbik<br> <p><b><i>Casben Lightfoot</i></b>, Grumpy ol' Rake from Tunare<br><b><i>Sabbik Silvertongue</i></b>, cleric of the Tinker's Pride</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umistressoftherose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mistress of the Rose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Black Rose</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/01 10:47:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tinker's Pride</span><hr size=1> Great although it is not a simple item one of you does know human.  I was afraid I was going to have to kidnap one of you and teach you dark elvish.  The item I seek would require a master gnome's work but I can wait for one just wanting to get into contact with the Tinker's Guild as they would most likely be the ones overseeing all the Tinkering in the gnome community.  I shall give you a tell 1 month from now.<br><br>ooc- Tomorrow I will try and give you a tell and I believe the item is trivial at 180 or so <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But I am willing to pay good for it.  It would very much enhance the roleplay aspect of my character as she is obsessed with jewelcrafting <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucasbenlightfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casben Lightfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/13/01 3:20:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tinker's Pride</span><hr size=1> If the item is something from the moon of Luclin I do believe that they are very hard to make.   As for learning tinkering better... well it's hard because of the cost involved.  I've spent as much money as I could afford, and have only a skill of 68 up to now.  <br><br>now if you'd like to start an &quot;adopt a tinker&quot; fund, I'm sure we could make you all sorts of neat items!<br><br>What is it that you are looking for anyhow?  I must say I'm curious  *smiles*<br><br>/ooc gonna be around the gorge of xorbb tommorow for a guild hunt, try to /tell me... if I don't reply, keep trying. <p><b><i>Casben Lightfoot</i></b>, Grumpy ol' Rake from Tunare<br><b><i>Sabbik Silvertongue</i></b>, cleric of the Tinker's Pride</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umistressoftherose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mistress of the Rose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Black Rose</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/13/01 5:41:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tinker's Pride</span><hr size=1> Zsuzsana dreams of being the ultimate sage and jewelcrafter.  She does not really care about being able to kill people as she loves to just sit and fashion nice jewelry.  She also loves fashion and will walk around in her gossamer robe as she thinks it is eloquent.  The item wanted is the Geerlock Gem Setter which gives enhancements to jewelcrafting.  Combine that with the fact her first AA abilities, when she can, will be the jewelcrafting ones and I am one step closer to making her the character I dreamed her to be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucasbenlightfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casben Lightfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/13/01 5:45:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tinker's Pride</span><hr size=1> I'm told that item would require a Sensate reishi lens.  I have no idea where such a thing could be found... So perhaps while I continue practicing my trade, you can try to find a few of these lenses.  I have plans to craft many of these enhanced trade tools in the future.<br><br> <p><b><i>Casben Lightfoot</i></b>, Grumpy ol' Rake from Tunare<br><b><i>Sabbik Silvertongue</i></b>, cleric of the Tinker's Pride</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umistressoftherose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mistress of the Rose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Black Rose</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/13/01 6:17:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tinker's Pride</span><hr size=1> Zsuzsana also might be willing to share some funds to help get the tinker high enough to make them also.  Just depends on how hard it is the raise tinkering as I have never been a gnome <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubraellarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Braellarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/13/01 6:27:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tinker's Pride</span><hr size=1> Those particular fongus can be found in the Paludal Caverns.<br><br>I presume that is where you get the lense from.<br><br>I have not killed many of them so i cannot say.<br><br>To reach the caverns you cross a large bridge in the Fordel Section of shadowhaven, wich leads to the area. Sneek past the bandits and past the fiends, the mushroons are scattered around with the largest concentration at the top of the caverns. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucasbenlightfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Casben Lightfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/13/01 2:06:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tinker's Pride</span><hr size=1> I must have missed them on my way to the Shadeweaver's Thicket then, if they were in the northern end of the caverns.  I wasn't exactly in the mood to stop and chat with the natives... Almost wet my britches going through there<br><br>*shudders*<br><br>As for tinkering, it's very, very expensive.  The fund was more of a joke...  it took me about 200pp to gain those 18 points of skill.  And the next 30 or so will cost much much more than that.  But the Luclin items seem to have a much more reasonable cost than the old world things.  Items that require a part from some monster usually are cheaper to make.  Time will tell.<br><br><br> <p><b><i>Casben Lightfoot</i></b>, Grumpy ol' Rake from Tunare<br><b><i>Sabbik Silvertongue</i></b>, cleric of the Tinker's Pride</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umistressoftherose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mistress of the Rose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Black Rose</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/13/01 8:44:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tinker's Pride</span><hr size=1> Okay I am about to get off from Finals week    yeeeeck.<br><br>I will have more time to play if I can find a dedicated line in which I can use my computer on.  Sucks having a network card and not having the money to get a cable modem for 1 month <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br><br>But I should be able to get to play some. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uspinnerofmoonshadow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spinner of Moonshadow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/14/01 6:55:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Sensate Lenses</span><hr size=1> Yes, the sensate reishi live in the Paludal caverns.  The lenses are uncommon drop, but not too rare.  I do not believe they are magic or lore, so that won't be much of a problem unless they are no drop on another server (doubt it... they sell for about a gold each)  I don't know where they are deeper in the cavern but there is one that spawns right before the bandit camp when you are leaving shadow haven.  Interesting loot on some of the elders though.  A 5/20 monk/beastmaster fist.  Fascinating.  Like most things in the cavers, the mature reishi are about 14-16, and I believe the elders are 16-18.  Well, that's just my two bits. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=904.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=852.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=10><img src=http://www.firiona-vie.com/images/arfv.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.threadControl?topicID=888.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=888.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=888